President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Barbera Hale Thornhill as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Singapore. Thornhill is currently the president of Impact Design, an interior design firm in Los Angeles, and is involved in various philanthropic and cultural organizations. 

Additionally, Trump intends to nominate Bruce Poliquin as Director and designated Chair of the Securities Investor Protection Corporation for the remainder of a three-year term. 

In terms of appointments, Douglas Vincent-Lang is set to be appointed as the United States Commissioner of the United States Section of the Pacific Salmon Commission for the remainder of a four-year term.

Lastly, several individuals will be appointed as Members to the Federal Service Impasses Panel for five-year terms.